Components.Planar Forks:
The following table details the forks known to access most planes. "Material" is the substance out of which the fork was made, usually metal. For example, in general, [[gold]] led to [[upper planes]], while [[iron]] led to [[lower planes]]. Pure metals were used for [[inner planes]], while alloys of those metals led to the respective [[paraelemental planes]].{{Cite dragon/120/Plane Speaking|42-43}}

"Pitch" is the single note to which an individual fork was tuned. If a plane had layers, this note always led to the first layer of that plane. [[Quasi-elemental planes]] could be reached by using a fork tuned sharp for [[Positive energy|positive]] planes and flat for [[Negative energy|negative]] planes. "Chord", in the table, indicates that multiple forks were required to ring in harmony. Major chords usually took one to the second layer of a plane, while minor chords took one to the third layer. More complicated harmonies were rumored to be able to reach other layers.
